  "body": "# Bug Report\r\n\r\n\r\n## Problem \r\n\r\nThere are several ways to reproduce the issue. Also, the app behaves differently on iOS and Android. \r\n\r\n### 1. New account creation on Android\r\n\r\n**STR:**\r\n1. Install Status\r\n2. `Generate a new key` > Choose device as key storage > Create a password > Tap `Next` and quickly tap `Back`while processing is in progress\r\n3. Choose device as key storage and create a password again\r\n4. Tap `Next`\r\n\r\n**Actual result:** app crashes with `java.lang.NullPointerException`\r\n\r\nhttps://user-images.githubusercontent.com/67952253/188643626-526b50ab-0287-47bb-a74d-bc32cc132b20.mp4\r\n\r\n### 2. Migration from a regular account to Keycard on Android\r\n\r\n**STR:**\r\n1. Install Status\r\n2. Recover/create a regular account\r\n3. `Profile` > `Privacy and security` > `Manage keys and storage` > `Log out`\r\n4. Put a tick `Move keystore file` > `Enter seed phrase` > `Choose a storage` > `Keycard` > `Confirm`\r\n5. Enter password to move your data > `Confirm`\r\n6. Tap `Back` on the `Store your keys on Keycard` screen\r\n7. Select `Keycard` and enter the password again > `Confirm` > Complete the onboarding flow\r\n\r\n**Actual result:** app crashes with `java.lang.NullPointerException` after Keycard passcode confirmation\r\n\r\n### 3. Migration from a regular account to Keycard on iOS\r\nMost problematic one\r\n\r\nThere are the same steps to reproduce as in the previous scenario but the resulting behavior is different.\r\nYou can finish the migration process, but if you log out of the app once and try to log in again, you will get `Looks like you've tapped a wrong keycard` message.\r\nThe `lost or frozen card?` flow doesn't help either - when you try to log in after recovery, the multi-account \"loses\" the username and changes the user's picture (see video below). Thus, login is not possible until the application is reinstalled.\r\n\r\n\r\nhttps://user-images.githubusercontent.com/67952253/188650692-bae1873a-2036-47ec-a597-af27af01c9c8.MP4\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n### Additional Information\r\n\r\n- Status version: nightly 1.19\r\n- Operating System: Android, iOS\r\n\r\n\r\n",
